DM2AUD.original: ~z~Take charge of her, won't ya Niko.
~z~A whole lot of money and a good Korean kid ain't around no more because of you.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~就因为你，好好的钱跟朝鲜小子都没了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~That ain't good news. Take me back to land.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~That ain't good news. Take me back to land.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~There's only one thing that's gonna make me forget about this fuck up. See ya.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~只有一样东西能让我忘了这次失败。再见。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Me, Bucky and Aiden, we all cared about the same stuff.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我、Bucky还有Aiden，我们都有相同的信念。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Watch it, we're meant to be protecting Kim, not sinking him.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~注意点，我们要保护Kim，不是击沉他。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~It's like fucking Cain and Abel the two of us. No wonder I turned into the wreck you see before ya.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我们俩就像该隐跟亚伯*。也难怪我会变成你见过的那副熊样。~n~(圣经中的一对兄弟，该隐因嫉妒杀害了弟弟亚伯)

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Shit, we let the poor kid down.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Shit, we let the poor kid down.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~He's paying for protection, Niko. Protect him, why don't ya.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~He's paying for protection, Niko. Protect him, why don't ya.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Shit, can't they let us go about our activities in peace.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Shit, can't they let us go about our activities in peace.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Shit, I think he ain't gonna last much longer.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Shit, I think he ain't gonna last much longer.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Get over it, Derrick. He was a smuggler and the cash was fake. I'll see you around.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~让它过去吧，Derrick。他是个走私者，钱也是假钞。我们之后见。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Jesus, I think this ship's about to go down with us in it.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Jesus, I think this ship's about to go down with us in it.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~As long as the ones he's paying us with are real, it doesn't matter.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~只要他给我们的报酬是真钞就行。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~This is a full on land and sea assault.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~This is a full on land and sea assault.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I don't give a shit as long as it keeps me in brown, you know.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我也不管这么多，能让我打海洛因就行，懂吧。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Shit, Niko. The Korean and his notes need our help.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Shit, Niko. The Korean and his notes need our help.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~The old dog still got some tricks.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~The old dog still got some tricks.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Couldn't see no other way how he got caught.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~想不到别的他会被抓的理由。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~It's the life blood of the place, people forget that.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~这才是这个国家的支柱，人们都忘了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Don't tell me you dropped something overboard.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~别跟我说你在船上落东西了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Come on, me boy. Get closer to Kim.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Come on, me boy. Get closer to Kim.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Fuck, that boat ain't looking too fresh.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Fuck, that boat ain't looking too fresh.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I guess I'm driving myself back. Bye.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~I guess I'm driving myself back. Bye.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Yeah. So Aiden got caught with something when he was somewhere he wasn't meant to be.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~对。然后Aiden在不该在的地方带着东西被抓了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Shit, they're sending the fucking airborne cavalry after us as well.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我靠，他们还他妈派空降兵来干我们了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Get in the boat, me boy. You're the skipper of this little vessel.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~快上船，小伙子。你就是这条小船的船长。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Christ, the notes may be fake but these bullets ain't. Get closer to Kim.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Christ, the notes may be fake but these bullets ain't. Get closer to Kim.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I don't reckon he's gonna hold up much longer.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~I don't reckon he's gonna hold up much longer.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~If the shoe fits, Niko. If the bloody shoe fits.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~只能这么解释了，Niko。就没别的解释。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Escorting a Korean contact of mine into the country with a boat load of fake hundred dollar bills.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~护送我的朝鲜联络人入境，他的船上装满了百元假钞。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I don't reckon this vessel will hold up much longer.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~I don't reckon this vessel will hold up much longer.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~More on the coast. They really want to take us down.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~More on the coast. They really want to take us down.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Niko, me boy. Packie tells me you got some sea legs on ya.
~z~Good thing the DTs ain't come in yet.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Good thing the DTs ain't come in yet.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~A rocket launcher. It's in the back. Get rid of the chopper with it. I'll drive the boat.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~火箭发射器，就在后头。拿它把那架直升机打下来，船我替你开。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Needless to say, he'll be inside for a time. Him and Bucky think I talked.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~想都不用想，他肯定得进去一段时间。他和Bucky觉得是我告发的。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~You're manning this yacht for us, Niko.
~z~So, is Francis the only explanation for this shit?
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~这些破事就只能怪到Francis头上吗？

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Me brothers were right to trust ya, Niko.
~z~They make these things in North Korea and have to ship 'em out here.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~他们在朝鲜印的，运过来了才能用。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~This deal should mean I can take care of me self.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~这次交易意味着我能独立生存了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Wanted a local to escort their boat into the harbor.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~想找个本地人护送他们的船到码头。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I may be jonesing but I can still shoot straight.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~I may be jonesing but I can still shoot straight.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Think of them notes, Niko. Protect Kim's boat.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Think of them notes, Niko. Protect Kim's boat.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Best way to avoid checks. We'll cover your rear.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~回避检查的最佳路径。我们会保护好你的。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Fucked if I know. Maybe me phone's tapped.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我他妈哪知道。可能我的电话被监听了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Good thing we got a rocket launcher with us.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~幸好我们这儿有火箭发射器。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Maybe Frankie has been tapping Ma's fucking phone and he called this in to mess with me.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~说不定Frankie这厮一直在偷听妈的电话，这群人就是他派来搞我的。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Seems like a good kid, reminds me of you actually.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~看起来是个好孩子，看着他我就想到你了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Shit. They're on the coastline. Can't even dock here.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Shit. They're on the coastline. Can't even dock here.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Shit, Derrick. You sound almost like a human being. I might just see you there.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~妈的，Derrick。你这是活过来了啊。我们码头见吧。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I owe ya an apology, Niko. I was dosed when you told me you'd killed Bucky and his boys.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我欠你一句道歉，Niko。你跟我说你杀了Bucky和他的手下的时候我刚好药嗑多了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I've heard it's some government funded operation.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~听说这还是什么政府出资的行动。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~You can't leave those notes out there without protection, Niko.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~You can't leave those notes out there without protection, Niko.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Jesus, helicopters ain't my idea of fun.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Jesus, helicopters ain't my idea of fun.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Think I gotta clue? Use our boat to shield Kim from these fuckers.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我咋知道？用我们的船从这些狗逼手里保护Kim。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Fuck, he's come all this way and it looks like he's gonna end up in the drink.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Fuck, he's come all this way and it looks like he's gonna end up in the drink.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~You got better things to be doing than take a swim, Niko.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~比起下水游泳，你还有更好的选择，Niko。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~He's bringing Super Notes into the country tonight.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~今晚他要把超级钞偷运入境。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I wasn't prepared for this type of attack.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~I wasn't prepared for this type of attack.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Here we are. Got him here in one piece. That was the deal. Thanks, Niko.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我们到了，把他安全护送到这儿了。就这点事，谢了，Niko。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Looks like we're about to end up in the drink, Niko.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Looks like we're about to end up in the drink, Niko.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~We're rendezvousing out at sea. This is the place.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我们要在海上碰头，那个位置。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Meet me at the jetty off a Rand Avenue. I need some help with something.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~来Rand大道边的码头找我，我需要你帮忙。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~That's all you can hope for in this God forsaken world. See you round, Niko.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~在这个被神抛弃的世界也没别的指望了。回头见，Niko。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~They're buzzing like hornets up there, Christ.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~They're buzzing like hornets up there, Christ.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~When this is done I won't have to leech off my brothers no more.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~这票成了以后，我就不用再啃家里兄弟的钱了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Over there, we used to buy 'em off him off of him then exchange 'em for genuine currency.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~在爱尔兰的时候，我们就问他买假钞，然后再洗成真钱。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Fuck! You'd think the Coastguard had drowning kids to save.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Fuck! You'd think the Coastguard had drowning kids to save.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I didn't think he even knew I was back. Can't the man just let his brother be?
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我都没想到他居然知道我回来了。这家伙就不能放他兄弟一马吗？

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I'd rather swim home tonight than come back tomorrow to dive for those notes.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我宁可今晚游泳回家，也不要明天再来捞钱。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I hope the rest of your time here is more peaceful.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~希望你在这里的余下时间可以安宁。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~It's in the hands of the Lord now.
~z~Shit, I hope me dealer will front me another dime bag. I'll call ya, Niko.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~操蛋，希望卖我毒品的人肯让我再赊一包。过会儿再联系，Niko。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Christ alive, they're attacking from the shoreline.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Christ alive, they're attacking from the shoreline.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I guess someone tipped these guys off.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~I guess someone tipped these guys off.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Only place for it, me boy. Only place for it. See you soon.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~只会花在那儿，小伙子。只会花在那儿的。之后见。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Good thing your aim is steadier than mine. You can drive the boat again now.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~幸好你的准头比我好。你可以回来开船了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I don't give a shit if this thing sinks, we got to protect him.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我他妈才不管这条船的死活，能保住Kim就行。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~They're cutting you in on this deal?
~z~Don't worry Kim, we're looking after you.
~z~Another immigrant, arriving in this city, trying to make something of himself.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~又一个移民来到了这座城市，想让自己有所成就。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Kim, we got you and them notes looked after.
~z~The bastards are firing from the shore.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~The bastards are firing from the shore.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I don't know. I told my dealer I was good for the money I owed him.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~不知道。我跟卖我毒品的人说过我很快就能把欠他的钱还上了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Nothing like thieves thieving off a thieves.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Nothing like thieves thieving off a thieves.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Don't put all the pay off up your arm, Derrick.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~别把这些钱全部花在给自己扎针上，Derrick。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Doesn't look like the arrival of these notes was such a secret. Can you think of why that is?
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~走私钞票的消息好像保密不够到位嘛？你知道咋回事吗？

DM2AUD.original: ~z~When you put it like that, he reminds me of a McReary. Good luck to him.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~你这么一说，倒让我想起某个姓McReary的了。祝他好运。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Fuck, imagine who'd turn up if it was real notes he was bringing into the country.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~操，要是他船上的是真钞，来的人可能更多。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~We got to make sure these notes make it, just to piss off Frankie if nothing else.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我们一定要把这些钞票送到，不为别的，就是要气死Frankie。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Don't leave him alone out there, Niko.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Don't leave him alone out there, Niko.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Nice scam if you don't hit the same place too often. His boys are pulling the same gig over here.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~不盯着一个地方洗就不会被发现。他的人要在这里来这套。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Get me back to land. I'll give you a call.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Get me back to land. I'll give you a call.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~You're a good man to have on side, Niko.
~z~This is nothing, Kim. You and them notes are gonna be fine.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~没问题的，Kim。你和钞票不会有事的。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Shit, man. I'm jonesing a bit. Bring me back to land.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~靠，老兄，我有点犯瘾了。送我回陆地。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I thought you was taking me to the coast? See ya, man.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~I thought you was taking me to the coast? See ya, man.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Is that because he's coming into the country to rob the good people of America of their hard earned money?
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~是不是因为他入境也是来掠夺美国好人的血汗钱的？

DM2AUD.original: ~z~You were meant to use that on choppers. Not the guy we're protecting.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~那玩意是用来打飞机的，不是打保护对象的。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Anyway, I figured you'd know a thing or two about smuggling stuff into the country.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~再说，你对怎么把东西偷运入境应该也略知一二。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~That's what everyone in this country wants, right?
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~That's what everyone in this country wants, right?

DM2AUD.original: ~z~They're coming at us head on, Niko.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~They're coming at us head on, Niko.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~From what I hear, Aiden still rants about me to anyone who'll listen.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我听说，Aiden现在还在跟别人抹黑我。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Thank you Mr. McReary. Not such smooth journey.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~谢谢你，McReary先生。路上有点不太顺啊。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I haven't felt safe since Aiden O'Malley went inside.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~自从Aiden O'Malley进局子以后，我就没觉得安全过。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~They got the whole navy out tonight!
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~They got the whole navy out tonight!

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Good shooting, kid. Take charge of her again, will ya?
~z~This is a Korean guy I did business with back in Ireland.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~这次是个以前在爱尔兰跟我做过生意的朝鲜人。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Don't shoot Kim. The fucking notes might catch fire.
~z~Shit, there goes pay day. At least he died rich, eh?
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Shit, there goes pay day. At least he died rich, eh?

DM2AUD.original: ~z~He's going to wish he never left home.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~He's going to wish he never left home.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~What is this? Get me back to solid ground.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~什么情况？让我回去脚踏实地吧。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~This is a country founded by immigrants.
~z~Yeah, got a bit hairy out there. Good thing you have your sea legs.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~确实，出了点小意外。还好你不会晕船。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~What's happening out there? I didn't think you had many friends left.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~出海干什么？我还以为你没剩下几个朋友了。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I'm gonna go drown my sorrows. I'll speak to you soon.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我只能回去借毒消愁了。之后再打给你。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~And Frankie's the biggest damn rat I know.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~而Frankie是我知道的最可能泄密的家伙。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Shit, Niko. Our boat's about to fall apart.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Shit, Niko. Our boat's about to fall apart.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~People who'll beg, steal and borrow to get ahead.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~讨饭、做贼、躲债的人才会往这儿来。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~At least I thought I believed in it. I was young.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~至少我觉得是信的。那会儿我还年轻。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~You know how to handle yourself, Niko.
~z~I'm starting to get sea sick, Niko. Take me back to the coast.
~z~Sure, I been telling a few people about this, but, hell, I smell a rat.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~的确，我有跟别人说过这事。不过，妈的，肯定是有人泄密。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Not such a warm welcome, is it?
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Not such a warm welcome, is it?

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I guess these guys want a slice of Kim's pie.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~I guess these guys want a slice of Kim's pie.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~This is what gets me out of bed in the morning!
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~This is what gets me out of bed in the morning!

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I know how it feels to be betrayed.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我知道被人背叛是什么感觉。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Come on, man. I thought you was taking me back to land?
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~拜托，老兄。你这是想把我往陆地上带吗？

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Fuck, imagine who'd turn up if it was real notes he was bringing into the country.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~操，要是他船上的是真钞，来的人可能更多。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Yeah, welcome to America. We're meeting your friends in Bohan. I'll text ya the route you got to take.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~对，欢迎来到美国。我们要去Bohan和你的朋友碰头。要走的路线我会发给你。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I never get tired of this shit!
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~I never get tired of this shit!

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Come on, Niko. I didn't sign up for no pleasure cruise.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~拜托，Niko。我不是出来邮轮观光的。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~We came together for a cause we believed in.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~我们都相信同一件事，才会走到一起。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Jesus, Niko. Don't let him hang like this.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Jesus, Niko. Don't let him hang like this.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Counterfeits. They look so good you wouldn't spot 'em in a month of Sundays.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~就是假钞。成色很好，仔细看都看不出来。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Him and them notes ain't gonna do shit for us no more. Let's go back to land.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~Him and them notes ain't gonna do shit for us no more. Let's go back to land.

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Sort your shit out. Get back in the boat so we can look for Kim.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~你丫适可而止一点。回船上来，我们好跟着Kim。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~You're illegal, right? You think us McRearys was legal when we came here?
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~你是非法移民，对吧？你以为我们McReary家族刚来这儿的时候就是合法公民吗？

DM2AUD.original: ~z~Maybe a few people at the pub I borrowed money from, as well. You'll say anything for a fix.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~也可能是酒馆里借给我钱的人。为了毒品你什么都会说。

DM2AUD.original: ~z~I ain't going for a swim with ya, Niko. Later on.
DM2AUD.translated: ~z~I ain't going for a swim with ya, Niko. Later on.
